---
title: Honey Lemon Trout with Spiced Dukkah over Rice Pilaf with Tomato Salsa
description: Dukkah—pronounced “doo-kah”—is a traditional Egyptian blend of nuts, seeds, and warm spices that livens up any dish with flavor and texture. In this recipe, you’ll toast our take on dukkah, then sprinkle the mix over roasted trout that's drizzled in a creamy honey lemon sauce. Everything’s served over rice pilaf with carrots and pickled raisins, alongside a fresh tomato salsa.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/honey-lemon-trout-with-spiced-dukkah-8c498e2f.jpg
